        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 8:17PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 817 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Morganton, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Morganton, Valdese, Drexel, Rutherford College, Lake Rhodhiss,
Connelly Springs, and Oak Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
